lar, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":42,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":51,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":86,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":117,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Joan Tatteshall was born in 1173, in Odell, Bedfordshire, England as the daughter of John Tatteshall. She married John Le Stedeman in 1193, in Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1173–":"1173–Surnud","1173–Female":"1173–Surnud","1171–1199":"1171–1199","1196–1225":"1196–1225","–Male":"Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1199":"1199","1196":"1196","1173":"1173","1193":"1193","1171":"1171","1290":"1290","Kent Co., Eng":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Odell, Bedfordshire, England":"Odell, Bedfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1173–":"1173–Kuollut","1173–Female":"1173–Kuollut","1171–1199":"1171–1199","1196–1225":"1196–1225","–Male":"Kuollut","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1199":"1199","1196":"1196","1173":"1173","1193":"1193","1171":"1171","1290":"1290","Kent Co., Eng":"Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Odell, Bedfordshire, England":"Odell, Bedfordshire, England"},"fr":{"1173–":"1173–Décédée","1173–Female":"1173–Décédée","1171–1199":"1171–1199","1196–1225":"1196–1225","–Male":"Décédé","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1199":"1199","1196":"1196","1173":"1173","1193":"1193"